Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: We are where we are because of fundamentals. Tech and the promise of what it can bring has sustained our market position. Yes it sucks that our fiat and BTC value have gone down, but there are many other projects ahead of us in 2018 that are off the first 100 projects now.

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: Going from <50 to <20 is much easier than <200 to <20

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content: So design decisions aside, if you dont believe in the tech, the team will disappoint you on hype/marketing. If you are in it for the tech and the betterment of this whole space, a misstep here and there is fine when the end result is revolutionary tech that has MASSIVE utility potential.

Author: KomodoWorld#8282
Content: the silence about Komodo from large twitter CT and VC, reddit and main crypto news websites is deafening. You could almost believe it didn't exist. Now I find it almost amusing, I know it will take time but everything is set for organic growth and continue improvements. The amazing thing is there are actual products being built on it while so few are taking notice.

Author: hyperDEX#6586
Content:
The whole point here is we get a POC out, the iterate until we get it to a point where normal users can use it. If we dont do that, we are not innovating, we are just coping what others have done. As i said many times before, we are designing things for the future, not the present. This is how you will know that we will be in a great position when the need becomes apparent.

DEX may not have been a critical need a year ago, CEX is fine, but in the next 6 months is where the war with crypto will start. As much hype and marketing you may have for a project, if you cannot fulfill the needs of the users, they will migrate to someone that can. This is where we are at right now.
